---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LegalArticle from '../components/LegalArticle.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="Refund and cancellation terms for FeatureSignals subscriptions and paid IT services."
>
  <LegalArticle title="Refund Policy">
    <p>
      This Refund Policy applies to paid subscriptions and fees for <strong>FeatureSignals</strong> hosted services (our SaaS offering). It is written in line with common practices
      for Indian and international software companies: clear trial terms, subscription billing rules, and how to contact us if something goes wrong.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Nature of the product</h2>
    <p>
      FeatureSignals provides <strong>digital IT services</strong> (access to software hosted by us). Fees cover ongoing access, support tiers as described in your plan, and related
      infrastructure—not physical goods.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Free trial</h2>
    <p>
      Where we offer a free trial, you can use the service for the stated trial period without charge unless you add a payment method and explicitly upgrade to a paid plan.
      If you do not subscribe before the trial ends, access to paid features may end automatically.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Subscription fees</h2>
    <p>
      Paid plans are generally billed in advance on a recurring basis (for example, monthly or annually) as shown at checkout or in your account. By subscribing, you authorize us
      and our payment partners to charge the applicable fees using your chosen payment method.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Cancellations</h2>
    <p>
      You may cancel your subscription through the billing settings in your account or by contacting <a href="mailto:support@featuresignals.com">support@featuresignals.com</a>.
      Cancellation stops future renewals; it does not automatically delete your data immediately—retention and export options are described in our terms of service and product documentation.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Refunds</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Billing errors:</strong> If you believe you were charged incorrectly, contact us within <strong>14 days</strong> of the charge. After we verify an error attributable to us
        or our payment processor, we will correct the charge or issue a refund to the original payment method where possible.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Duplicate charges:</strong> Accidental duplicate payments will be refunded after verification.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>General policy:</strong> Except as above or as required by applicable law, subscription fees are <strong>non-refundable</strong> once the billing period has started,
        because the service is delivered continuously during that period. We do not provide partial refunds for unused time when you cancel mid-cycle unless we agree otherwise in writing
        or the law in your jurisdiction requires it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Statutory rights:</strong> Nothing in this policy limits mandatory consumer rights that cannot be waived under the laws of India or your country of residence.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Downgrades and plan changes</h2>
    <p>
      If you move to a lower tier or reduce seats, pricing adjustments will apply from the next billing cycle unless we specify otherwise at the time of the change.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Chargebacks and disputes</h2>
    <p>
      Please contact us before initiating a chargeback so we can resolve the issue. Unresolved chargebacks may result in suspension of access until the dispute is cleared.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Open-source self-hosting</h2>
    <p>
      The FeatureSignals software is available under the Apache-2.0 license for self-hosting. This Refund Policy applies to <strong>paid hosted services from us</strong>, not to
      third-party infrastructure or support you purchase elsewhere.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For refund and billing questions, email <a href="mailto:support@featuresignals.com">support@featuresignals.com</a> with your account email and invoice or transaction reference if available.
    </p>
  </LegalArticle>
</Layout>
